{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["A fast alternative to displacement that only modifies normals to give the appearance of surface height variations. The surface offset is defined by the ", {"text": ["value"], "type": "ui"}, " input. The position isn\u2019t modified."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "div", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "displacetype_bump"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Sets the normal to the vector ", {"text": ["value"], "type": "ui"}, ", after converting from the set ", {"text": ["Normal Space"], "type": "ui"}, " and applying any flipping as defined by ", {"text": ["Flip X"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Flip Y"], "type": "ui"}, ". The normal is applied relative to the chosen ", {"text": ["Space"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "div", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "displacetype_normal"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Offsets ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "ui"}, " by a component of ", {"text": ["value"], "type": "ui"}, " in the direction of ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "ui"}, ". Updates ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "ui"}, " to fit the new surface positions."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "div", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "displacetype_dispnormal"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Offsets ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "ui"}, " by the ", {"text": ["value"], "type": "ui"}, " vector. The ", {"text": ["value"], "type": "ui"}, " is applied in the chosen ", {"text": ["Space"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "div", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "displacetype_dispvector"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Causes reflections to be stretched in the direction defined by ", {"text": ["Anisotropy Direction"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["This simulates microscopic bumps with a directional bias, causing light to be scattered more in the defined direction. This is typical of brushed metals."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_aniso.png", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_aniso.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link"}]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "aniso"}}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The effect of this parameter increases with ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, ". It has no effect at all when ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " is ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "aniso_notes"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Controls the direction of ", {"text": ["Anisotropy"], "type": "ui"}, " relative to the UV coordinates of the surface. At ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, ", reflections are stretched in the ", {"text": ["U"], "type": "ui"}, " direction. At ", {"text": ["0.5"], "type": "code"}, ", the direction is rotated by ", {"text": ["90 degrees"], "type": "code"}, " to the ", {"text": ["V"], "type": "ui"}, " direction. ", {"text": ["1.0"], "type": "code"}, " equals ", {"text": ["180"], "type": "code"}, " degrees. Since the effect is symmetrical this produces the same result as ", {"text": ["0.0"], "type": "code"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The direction of rotation also depends on the UV layout. When the UVs are layed out such that textures appear on the surface without mirroring, higher values rotate counter-clockwise."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_anisodir.png", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_anisodir.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link"}]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "text": ["The effect of this parameter diminishes with decreasing ", {"text": ["Roughness"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Anisotropy"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}], "indent": 4, "role": "item", "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "anisodir"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Shade both sides of a surface as if they were the front side."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Any transparent part of the shader is unaffected, since transparency relies\n    on the orientation of surfaces to function correctly."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "frontface_shader"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Tint rays with this color as they pass through an object. The amount\n    of tinting depends on the distance travelled."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "transcolor"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["The travel distance necessary for the specified__Transmission Color__ to\n    be reached. Shorter distances result in less, greater distances\n    in more tinting."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_transdist.png", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_transdist.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link"}]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "transdist"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Spreads and colors refraction rays to simulate the effect of a spectrum of\n    wavelengths within the refracted light."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["This value is a spread around the specified ", {"text": ["IOR"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": [{"_hs_sc": true, "text": "", "value": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_dispersion.png", "fullpath": "/images/nodes/vop/principled_shader_dispersion.png", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link"}]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "dispersion"}}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Specifies the priority used with Nested Dielectrics."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "text": ["Requires ", {"text": ["Enable Absorption and Nested Dielectrics"], "type": "ui"}, " to be enabled on the\n    ", {"_hs_sc": true, "text": ["Mantra render node"], "value": "/nodes/out/ifd", "fullpath": "/nodes/out/ifd", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "tag": "dev", "type": "pxml", "attrs": {"id": "priority"}}], "type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "include"}}